{
  "stem": "10353.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And on September the 1st, we got to know that Hitler invaded Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were in relative-- in relative security at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we heard what was going on, and we felt very upset-- knowing what was happened to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But we did not realize-- realize the extent of the danger that was really facing the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The first sense that we got about the great danger was already later on in-- in 19-- January, I believe, January, 1940.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Prior to that, in September, the 5th of 1940, we were occupied by the Hungarians, part of Transylvania was occupied by the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, overnight, we became Hungarian citizens, so to say.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were already allied with the Germans by that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And some anti-Jewish laws were coming out slowly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Like Jews, for instance, couldn't go to the market, shopping, till 10 o'clock to give-- to give more time for the non-Jewish population to go to the market first.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They wouldn't issue any new-- any licenses for Jewish businesses.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the so-called undercurrent was coming through the surface.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there were anti-Semitic manifestations by more repeated beatings of Jews, and sort of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] physically abusing 'em.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] They probably did, but they didn't go too far.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For the Hungarians, you didn't go too far.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were-- was the Romanians-- you could buy your way out many times.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You couldn't do that with the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were also dominated very strongly by the German anti-Jewish policies.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nonetheless, we could still breathe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We could still live, even though they have instituted, by that time, numerus nullus-- in other words, Jews couldn't-- Jews couldn't go to colleges.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
